{
  "stem": "27340.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it wasn't until my father was taken into concentration camp in Buchenwald that my mother, who was then left alone, as it were, as far as our family was concerned, actually started working very, very hard and trying to get out.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we did obtain an affidavit, I understand, to enter the United States by 1943.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Now, don't forget, we are still now in 1939, so that meant another four years of hell, of possible total annihilation.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "One didn't know what was likely to happen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so the situation became fairly, fairly dicey.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The amazing thing is we lived in a very large house.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And after, after, after possibly 1937 or '38, my-- our family, my father, mother, brother, and myself, moved into this particular house that was property of my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Families tended to sort of close up a little bit more.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It gave them moral support.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was economically sound.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so we lived in this very big house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the house was taken care of by a caretaker, who also had an accommodation in this house in the basement.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He, his wife, and two sons were living there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they were not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And during the atrocities of the destruction of the synagogues and Jewish shops that started at the Kristallnacht, round about 12 o'clock midnight on that very day or at the end of that very day, the Gestapo came in order to collect my father and my grandfather to be carted off to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And this caretaker, who was a member of the Nazi party, opened the gates and told them that they had already been collected.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, indeed.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that literally saved them from-- and so the Nazis went away, trusting the information to be correct.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
